If a sword is supposed to be flat, atleast mention that it is in the first post. If this were fully 3D, I would say it’s a nice model, but for now, I can only say it’s a nice cardboard cutout :S it only looks like cardboard because you extruded it a very small amount.

Oh yea, I wouldn’t go around calling one of the community’s BEST modelers a douche, it just makes you look more like one.

ONE LAST THING! STOP REPEATING THINGS THAT PEOPLE SAID, IT DOESN’T GET FUNNY THE SECOND TIME!

Secondly, I never said that it looked like cardboard to be funny in any way, I was explaining how it looks like cardboard.

And yea, I know what you mean im_mad. But you really can’t take it that hard, and you really have to expect it when your model is almost entirely a trace. Also, don’t expect everyone to love your model or comment nicely on it, especially being it’s only V1. You should really improve it, give it some shape and volume, and then maybe it will come out better. Just keep a backup incase something goes wrong, like you save it after screwing up bad on it.[/quote]i referring to the other douche bags, you supplied him with criticism, I’m personally not against that but as I said don’t put dylan above others just because he can model moderately well.
